      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so i got a 2018 camry in the shop and it's throwing a p0171 code. i already checked the maf sensor and it seems fine, readings look okay. what else should i be looking at for a lean condition?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A p0171 code indicates a lean condition in the engine, meaning there's too much air and not enough fuel. Given that you've checked the Mass Air Flow (MAF) sensor and it's reading correctly, the next step is to examine the fuel injectors. They could be clogged or leaking, causing an imbalance in the air-fuel mixture. You might also want to check the fuel pressure regulator and the fuel pump. If these components are not functioning properly, they could also lead to a lean condition. Remember, a lean condition can be quite dangerous, so it's important to address it promptly. If you're not comfortable doing this yourself, consider taking your Camry to a professional mechanic. They can help ensure that all the components are working correctly and that your car is running smoothly.",
